public class GeneratorGlobalTesterModel
extends fr.sorbonne_u.components.cyphy.utils.tests.AbstractTestScenarioBasedAtomicModel
implements TankLevelManagementI
    The class GeneratorGlobalTesterModelimplements a model that executes global test scenarios for the generator.

    Description

    This atomic HIOA simulation model is defined as solely executing test scenarios (@see fr.sorbonne_u.components.hem2025.tests_utils.AbstractTestScenarioBasedAtomicHIOA) for more explanations.

    Compared to GeneratorUnitTesterModel, this model only imports and exports the external events not related to the continuous variables of the generator models. In the global simulator, these continuous variables are shared by the ElectricMeterElectricityModel instead.

    • Imported events: TankEmpty, TankNoLongerEmpty
    • Exported events: Start, Stop, Refill
    • Imported variables: none
    • Exported variables: none

        create an atomic model with the given URI (if null, one will be generated) and to be run by the given simulator using the given time unit for its clock.

        Contract

         pre     uri == null || !uri.isEmpty()
 pre     simulatedTimeUnit != null
 pre     simulationEngine != null && !simulationEngine.isModelSet()
 pre     simulationEngine instanceof AtomicEngine
 post    !isDebugModeOn()
 post    getURI() != null && !getURI().isEmpty()
 post    uri == null || getURI().equals(uri)
 post    getSimulatedTimeUnit().equals(simulatedTimeUnit)
 post    getSimulationEngine().equals(simulationEngine)
        Parameters:
        uri - unique identifier of the model.
        simulatedTimeUnit - time unit used for the simulation clock.
        simulationEngine - simulation engine enacting the model.
